d their first single 'Ruth' from their upcoming album. Go to there page to check it\u2026\"|website=Instagram|language=en|access-date=2019-01-22}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\nIn 2014, Heaton played a role in a short film named \"[https://www.imdb.com/title/tt9217058/?ref_=nm_flmg_act_14 Life Needs Courage]\". In 2015, he made his acting debut with the [[ITV (TV network)|ITV]] crime drama series ''[[DCI Banks]]'', playing the role of Gary McCready.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Robinson|first1=Jennifer|title=DCI BANKS: Season 4|url=http://www.kpbs.org/news/2015/apr/23/dci-banks-season-4/|accessdate=3 September 2015|work=KPBS.org|date=23 April 2015}}</ref> He then appeared as Riley in [[ITV (TV network)|ITV]]'s detective series ''[[Vera (TV series)|Vera]]''.<ref>{{cite web|title=Vera Cast List 2015: ITV Series 5 Air Date and Character Details|url=http://tellychat.co.uk/vera-series-5-itv-2015-starts-filming-vera-stanhope-new-episodes-0445|website=TellyChat.co.uk|accessdate=3 September 2015}}</ref> He guest-starred in [[BBC One]]'s medical drama series ''[[Casualty (TV series)|Casualty]]'' as Jason Waycott.<ref>{{cite web|title=The Department of Secrets \u2013 Series 29 Episode 31 of 46|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b05tqxbb|publisher=BBC|accessdate=3 September 2015}}</ref> In 2016, he appeared in the thriller film ''[[Shut In (2016 film)|Shut In]]'', co-starring [[Naomi Watts]] and [[Oliver Platt]], and directed by [[Farren Blackburn]].<ref>{{cite magazine|last1=Hipes|first1=Patrick|title=Oliver Platt Joins Naomi Watts In 'Shut In' For EuropaCorp & Lava Bear|url=https://deadline.com/2015/03/oliver-platt-shut-in-movie-naomi-watts-1201394566|accessdate=3 September 2015|magazine=Deadline.com|date=18 March 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=McNary|first1=Dave|title=Naomi Watts' ''Shut In'' Set 2016 Release Date|url=https://variety.com/2015/film/news/naomi-watts-shut-in-sullivan-stapletons-the-lake-set-2016-release-dates-1201448033|accessdate=3 September 2015|website=Variety|date=6 March 2015}}</ref> Heaton also plays Jonathan Byers in the [[Netflix]] supernatural drama series ''[[Stranger Things (TV series)|Stranger Things]]''.<ref>{{cite magazine|last1=Andreeva|first1=Nellie|title=Duffer Bros. Netflix Supernatural Drama Series Sets Young Cast, Gets Title|url=https://deadline.com/2015/08/duffer-bros-netflix-series-stranger-things-young-cast-1201502552|accessdate=3 September 2015|magazine=Deadline.com|date=20 August 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Spangler|first1=Todd|title=Netflix Casts 7 Young Actors in ''Stranger Things'' Supernatural Drama from Duffer Brothers|url=https://variety.com/2015/digital/news/netflix-stranger-things-duffer-brothers-winona-ryder-1201574835|accessdate=28 August 2016|website=Variety|date=20 August 2015}}</ref> In 2016, he starred in the movie ''[[As You Are (film)|As You Are]]''.\n\nIn May 2017, Heaton was cast to star as [[Cannonball (comics)|Samuel \"Sam\" Guthrie / Cannonball]] in ''[[New Mutants (film)|New Mutants]]'', a 2020 film based on the [[Marvel Comics]] comic book of the [[New Mutants|same name]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://collider.com/new-mutants-movie-cannonball-charlie-heaton/|title='New Mutants' Finds Its Cannonball with 'Stranger Things' Star Charlie Heaton|last=Goldberg|first=Matt|work=Collider|date=31 May 2017|accessdate=31 May 2017}}</ref> In August 2018, the BBC announced that Heaton would be playing [[Joseph Merrick]], commonly known as the \"Elephant Man\", in a new two-part drama.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/mediacentre/latestnews/2018/the-elephant-man|title=Charlie Heaton is The Elephant Man|publisher=BBC|date=22 August 2019|accessdate=22 January 2019}}</ref> The casting drew criticism from a disability charity group, the group's head saying that not using a disabled actor was a missed opportunity.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://news.sky.com/story/anger-over-casting-of-stranger-things-star-charlie-heaton-as-elephant-man-11485440|title=Anger over casting of Stranger Things star Charlie Heaton as Elephant Mann|publisher=Sky News|accessdate=22 January 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nHe has a son, Archie (born 2014), with his ex-girlfriend Akiko Matsuura [1]. Since 2016, he has been in a relationship with his ''Stranger Things'' co-star, [[Natalia Dyer]], who plays Jonathan's girlfriend [[Nancy Wheeler]] on the show.<ref>https://www.capitalfm.com/news/tv-film/stranger-things/natalia-dyer-charlie-heaton-relationship-timeline/</ref>\n\nHeaton missed the premiere of ''Stranger Things 2'' as on 21 October 2017. Heaton was detained at Los Angeles International Airport in October due to possession of trace amounts of cocaine, reports had said. He was not arrested and immediately returned to London. More than a week later, he said in a statement that his planned travel to the U.S. was \"affected by an issue at U.S. immigration\" and that he \"was not arrested or charged with a crime.\" <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.eonline.com/news/919917/stranger-things-charlie-heaton-opens-up-about-cocaine-possession-reports|title=Charlie Heaton Opens Up About Cocaine Possession Reports|last=|first=|date=2018-03-11|website=E! Online|language=en-US|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-01-23}}</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n\n===Film===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\"|2015\n| ''The Schoolboy''\n| Michael Stevens\n| Short film\n|-\n| ''Rise of the Footsoldier Part II''\n| Dealer\n| Originally titled: ''Reign of the General''\n|-\n| ''Urban & the Shed Crew''\n| Frank\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"|2016\n| ''[[As You Are (film)|As You Are]]''\n| Mark\n|\n|-\n| ''[[Shut In (2016 film)|Shut In]]''\n| Stephen Portman\n| \n|-\n|-\n| 2017\n| ''[[Marrowbone (film)|Marrowbone]]''\n| Billy\n| \n|-\n| 2020\n| ''[[The New Mutants (film)|The New Mutants]]''\n| [[Cannonball (comics)|Samuel Guthrie / Cannonball]]\n| Completed\n|-\n| TBA\n| ''[[The Souvenir Part II]]''\n|\n| Post-production\n|}\n\n===Television===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\"|2015\n| ''[[DCI Banks]]''\n| Gary McCready\n| 2 episodes\n|-\n| ''[[Vera (TV series)|Vera]]''\n| Riley\n| Episode: \"Changing Tides\"\n|-\n| ''[[Casualty (TV series)|Casualty]]''\n| Luke Dickinson, Jason Waycott\n| Episode: \"Sweetie\", Episode: \"The Department of Secrets\"\n|-\n| 2016\u2013present\n| ''[[Stranger Things]]''\n| Jonathan Byers\n| Main role\n|}\n\n==Awards and nominations==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Award\n! Category\n! Nominated work\n! Result\n! {{Abbr|Ref.|References}}\n|-\n|2017\n| [[Screen Actors Guild Award]]s\n| [[Screen Actors Guild Award for Outstanding Performance by an Ensemble in a Drama Series|Outstanding Performance by an Ensemble in a Drama Series]]\n| rowspan=\"3\" |''[[Stranger Things]]''\n| {{won}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | <ref>{{cite journal |url=https://www.ew.com/article/2016/12/14/2017-sag-awards-nominations |title=SAG Awards nominations 2017: See the full list |magazine=[[Entertainment Weekly]] |first=Joely |last=Nolfi |date=14 December 2016 |access-date=31 July 2018 |publisher=[[Meredith Corporation]]}}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=2|2018\n| [[Screen Actors Guild Award]]s\n| Outstanding Performance by an Ensemble in a Drama Series\n| {{nom}}\n|style=\"text-align:center;\" | <ref>{{cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2018/01/sag-awards-stunt-nominees-2018-john-bernecker-walking-dead-1202239125/ |title=SAG Awards' Stunt Ensemble Nominees Include Fallen 'Walking Dead' Stuntman |last=Hipes |first=Patrick |work=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |date=January 21, 2018 |access-date=January 11, 2018 |publisher=[[Penske Business Media, LLC.]]}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Teen Choice Awards]]\n| Choice Scene Stealer\n| {{nom}}\n|style=\"text-align:center;\" | <ref>{{cite web |url=https://tvline.com/2018/06/22/teen-choice-awards-2018-nominees-full-list-tv-nominations/ |title=Teen Choice Awards 2018: Riverdale Leads Final Wave of TV Nominations |last=Swift |first=Andy |work=[[TVLine]] |date=June 22, 2018 |access-date=June 22, 2018}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb name|6390427}}\n\n{{ScreenActorsGuildAwards EnsembleTVDrama 2010\u20132019}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Heaton, Charlie}}\n[[Category:1994 births]]\n[[Category:English male film actors]]\n[[Category:English male television actors]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Bridlington]]\n[[Category:Male actors from Leeds]]\n[[Category:21st-century English male actors]]\n[[Category:English drummers]]\n", "name_user": "2a00:23c7:3404:4500:2578:6964:dcab:4ac3", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "(\u2192\u200eEarly life)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Charlie_Heaton"}
{"title_page": "Afternoon Delight", "text_new": "{{other uses}}\n{{Infobox song\n| name       = Afternoon Delight\n| cover      = Afternoon Delight by The Starland Vocal Band.jpg\n| alt        =\n| type       = single\n| artist     = [[Starland Vocal Band]]\n| album      = Starland Vocal Band\n| B-side     = Starland\n| released   = April 1976\n| format     = [[7-inch single]]\n| recorded   = November 1975\n| studio     =\n| venue      =\n| genre      = [[Country pop]], [[soft rock]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.stereogum.com/5507/40_most_softsational_softrock_songs/franchises/list/|title=VH1\u2019s 40 Most Softsational Soft-Rock Songs|date=May 31, 2007|website=[[Stereogum]]|publisher=[[SpinMedia]]|access-date=July 31, 2016}}</ref>\n| length     = 3:16\n| label      =\n*[[Windstar Records|Windsong]] (US)\n*[[Leon Schlesinger|Windlands International]] (UK & Canada)\n| writer     = [[Bill Danoff]]\n| producer   = [[Milt Okun]]\n| prev_title =\n| prev_year  =\n| next_title = California Day\n| next_year  = 1976\n| misc       = {{external music video|header=Audio|{{youtube|XHMi_5a9Omg|\"Afternoon Delight\"}}}}\n}}\n\n\"'''Afternoon Delight'''\" is a hit song recorded by [[Starland Vocal Band]], known for its [[close harmony]] and sexually suggestive wordplay. It was written by [[Bill Danoff]], one of the members of the band.\n\n\"Afternoon Delight\" charted well in New Zealand, peaking at number five. In Australia it was a number-six hit ([[Adelaide]] radio station [[5MMM|5KA]] was first to pick up the single, making it number one in [[South Australia]]). In the UK, it reached number 18 and was used as theme to a weekly show of the same title on London's [[Capital London|Capital Radio]], hosted by [[Duncan Johnson]], and from 1980 on an afternoon show using the same title, broadcast every weekday at [[Mercia Sound]] in [[Coventry]], presented by [[Stuart Linnell]]. It became a US number-one single on July 10, 1976<ref name=\"Bronson\">{{cite book  | last = Bronson  | first = Fred  | authorlink = Fred Bronson  | title = The Billboard Book of Number 1 Hits  | edition = 5th  | year = 2003  | publisher = Billboard Books  | isbn = 0-8230-7677-6  | page = 438  | url = https://books.google.com/books?id=PgGqNrqfrsoC&pg=PT447&dq=%22Afternoon+Delight%22+0823076776&ei=BvTuS865DaHCzQT74t3GCg&cd=1#v=onepage&q&f=false  | chapter = Afternoon Delight}}</ref> and earned a [[Music recording sales certification|gold record]]. \"Afternoon Delight\" also reached number one in Canada.\n\n==Background and writing==\nThe title came from the [[happy hour]] menu at [[Clyde's Restaurant Group|Clyde's]] [[restaurant]] in [[Georgetown (Washington, D.C.)|Georgetown]], [[Washington, D.C.]]<ref name=\"Bronson\"/> where Bill Danoff was eating with fellow bandmember Margot Chapman while his then-wife [[Taffy Danoff]] was undergoing surgery for [[cervical cancer]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://patch.com/florida/safetyharbor/grammy-winner-taffy-nivert-settles-in-safety-harbor |title=Grammy Winner Taffy Nivert Settles In Safety Harbor - Safety Harbor, FL Patch |website=Patch.com |date=2013-02-08 |accessdate=2016-10-11}}</ref> Danoff enjoyed writing the song and downplayed the somewhat controversial lyrics, saying, \"I didn't want to write an all-out [[sexual intercourse|sex]] song ... I just wanted to write something that was fun and hinted at sex.\"<ref name=\"Bronson\"/>\n\n==Cover versions==\nConcurrent with the Starland Vocal Band version, country singer [[Johnny Carver (musician)|Johnny Carver]]'s cover went Top 10 on ''Billboard'' [[Hot Country Songs|Hot Country Singles]]. In 1983, the [[Circle Jerks]] also covered it as one of the six covers on \"Golden Shower of Hits (Jerks on 45)\", which appears on their album ''[[Golden Shower of Hits]]''. British experimental folk music band [[Current 93]] used an industrial-style cover as an introduction to performances of their 2009 album. [[Claude Fran\u00e7ois]] sang it in French as \"Dimanche apr\u00e8s-midi\". The popular TV show ''[[Glee (TV series)|Glee]]'' also covered it in their episode \"[[Sexy (Glee)|Sexy]]\", with [[Dianna Agron]], [[Jayma Mays]], [[Mark Salling]], [[Lea Michele]], and [[John Stamos]] singing.\n\n==Critical reaction==\nAt the [[19th Grammy Awards]] ceremony in 1977, \"Afternoon Delight\" received three nominations for recordings from 1976. It won the [[Grammy Award for Best Vocal Arrangement for Two or More Voices|Grammy Award for Best Arrangement for Voices]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.grammy.com/nominees/search?artist=starland+vocal+band&title=&year=All&genre=All |title=The Grammys : Starland Vocal Band : Search |website=Grammy.com |accessdate=2016-10-11}}</ref> and was also nominated for Best Pop Performance by a Duo or Group with Vocals and [[Grammy Award for Song of the Year|Song of the Year]].\n\nIn 2010 ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' named \"Afternoon Delight\" the 20th sexiest song of all time.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/959429/the-50-sexiest-songs-of-all-time-page-4 |title=The 50 Sexiest Songs Of All Time Page 4 |publisher=Billboard |date= |accessdate=2016-10-11}}</ref>\n\n==Chart performance==\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-2}}\n\n===Weekly charts===\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n!Chart (1976)\n!Peak<br />position\n|-\n| Australian Singles Chart\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|6\n|-\n|Canada ''[[RPM (magazine)|RPM]]'' Top Singles<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bac-lac.gc.ca/eng/discover/films-videos-sound-recordings/rpm/Pages/image.aspx?Image=nlc008388.4299a&URLjpg=http%3a%2f%2fwww.collectionscanada.gc.ca%2fobj%2f028020%2ff4%2fnlc008388.4299a.gif&Ecopy=nlc008388.4299a|title=Item Display - RPM - Library and Archives Canada |website=Collectionscanada.gc.ca |date=1976-08-07 |accessdate=2018-06-10}}</ref>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|1\n|-\n|Canada ''RPM'' Adult Contemporary<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bac-lac.gc.ca/eng/discover/films-videos-sound-recordings/rpm/Pages/image.aspx?Image=nlc008388.4151&URLjpg=http%3a%2f%2fwww.collectionscanada.gc.ca%2fobj%2f028020%2ff4%2fnlc008388.4151.gif&Ecopy=nlc008388.4151|title=Item Display - RPM - Library and Archives Canada |website=Collectionscanada.gc.ca |date=1976-07-10 |accessdate=2018-06-11}}</ref>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|6\n|-\n{{single chart|Dutch100|22|artist=Starland Vocal Band |song=Afternoon Delight}}\n|-\n{{single chart|New Zealand|5|artist=Starland Vocal Band |song=Afternoon Delight}}\n|-\n{{single chart|UKsinglesbyname|18|artist=Starland Vocal Band}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Billboardhot100|1|artist=Starland Vocal Band}}\n|-\n| US [[Adult Contemporary (chart)|Easy Listening]] (''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'')<ref>[https://www.billboard.com/music/Starland-Vocal-Band/chart-history/adult-contemporary \"Starland Vocal Band Chart History (Easy Listening)\"]. ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]''.</ref>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|5\n|-\n{{single chart|Billboardcountrysongs|94|artist=Starland Vocal Band}}\n|}\n{{col-2}}\n\n===Year-end charts===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Chart (1976)\n! Rank\n|-\n|Australia<ref name=\"australian-charts.com\">[http://australian-charts.com/forum.asp?todo=viewthread&id=40275 Australian-charts.com] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141006134948/http://australian-charts.com/forum.asp?todo=viewthread&id=40275 |date=2014-10-06 }}</ref>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|56\n|-\n|Canada ''RPM'' Top Singles<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.collectionscanada.gc.ca/rpm/028020-119.01-e.php?&file_num=nlc008388.5173a&type=1&interval=20&PHPSESSID=u9874ano8k0c5b6bkp4r8qrbp3 |title= Top Singles \u2013 Volume 26, No. 14 & 15, January 08 1977 |work= [[RPM (magazine)|RPM]] |publisher= [[Library and Archives Canada]] |accessdate= December 6, 2017 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20160319222559/http://www.collectionscanada.gc.ca/rpm/028020-119.01-e.php?&file_num=nlc008388.5173a&type=1&interval=20&PHPSESSID=u9874ano8k0c5b6bkp4r8qrbp3 |archive-date= 2016-03-19 |url-status= dead }}</ref>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|11\n|-\n|New Zealand <ref>http://nztop40.co.nz/chart/?chart=3865</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|28\n|-\n|UK <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.old-charts.com/charts70/yearend70/1976yearend_uk.htm |title=Old-Charts |publisher=Old-Charts |date= |accessdate=2015-11-12}}</ref>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|120\n|-\n|US ''Billboard'' Hot 100<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.musicoutfitters.com/topsongs/1976.htm |title=Top 100 Hits of 1976/Top 100 Songs of 1976 |website=Musicoutfitters.com |date= |accessdate=2016-10-11}}</ref>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|12\n|-\n|US ''Billboard'' Easy Listening<ref>[http://www.45cat.com/45_list_view_record.php?li=2171 Top 50 Adult Contemporary Hits of 1976]</ref>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|31\n|-\n|US ''Cash Box'' Top 100<ref>{{cite web|url=http://50.6.195.142/archives/70s_files/1976YESP.html |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2016-06-05 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141021102718/http://50.6.195.142/archives/70s_files/1976YESP.html |archivedate=2014-10-21 }}</ref>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|7\n|}\n\n===All-time charts===\n{|class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\"\n|-\n! Chart (1958-2018)\n! Position\n|-\n|US ''Billboard'' Hot 100<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/charts/hot-100-60th-anniversary|title=Billboard Hot 100 60th Anniversary Interactive Chart|work=Billboard|accessdate=10 December 2018}}</ref>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|419\n|}\n{{col-end}}\n\n=== Johnny Carver version ===\n{|class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Chart (1976)\n! Peak<br />position\n|-\n| US ''Billboard'' Hot Country Singles & Tracks\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|9\n|-\n| Canadian ''RPM'' Country Tracks\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|16\n|}\n\n==In popular culture==\n{{unreferenced section|date=September 2017}}\n{{reduce trivia|section|date=September 2017}}\nSince the original song's release, many works have alluded to or even featured \"Afternoon Delight\" or its suggestive lyrics. Among them have been ''[[Cocktail (1988 film)|Cocktail]]'' (\"[[Kokomo (song)|Kokomo]]\", sung by [[The Beach Boys]]), ''[[Glee (TV series)|Glee]]'' (where it was mistaken as a song celebrating America's 1976 Bicentennial), ''[[Get a Life (TV series)|Get a Life]]'' (\"Chris Wins a Celebrity\"), ''[[Good Will Hunting]]'', ''[[PCU (film)|PCU]]'' (forced listening as a form of torture), ''[[Boogie Nights]]'', ''[[Lost (TV series)|Lost]]'', ''[[The Rules of Attraction]]'', ''[[The Spirit of '76 (1990 film)|The Spirit of '76]]'', ''[[Starsky & Hutch (film)|Starsky & Hutch]]'', ''[[ER (season 9)|ER]]'' (\"No Strings Attached\", sung by [[Abby Lockhart|Abby]]), ''[[Arrested Development (TV series)|Arrested Development]]'' (as part of a plot point in the episode \"[[Afternoon Delight (Arrested Development episode)|Afternoon Delight]]\"), ''[[The Simpsons]]'' (\"[[The Fat and the Furriest]]\"), ''[[Rules of Engagement (TV series)|Rules of Engagement]]'', ''[[Sports Night]]'', ''[[Complete Savages]]'' (\"Teen Things I Hate About You\"), ''[[Ugly Betty]]'', ''[[Family Guy]]'', ''[[Malcolm in the Middle]]'', ''[[South Park]]'' (\"[[Miss Teacher Bangs a Boy]]\"), ''[[Murphy Brown]]'', ''[[Entourage (U.S. TV series)|Entourage]]'', ''[[Warehouse 13]]'' (Season 2 Episode 8), ''[[Teenage Caveman (2002 film)|Teenage Caveman]]'' and ''[[Anchorman: The Legend of Ron Burgundy]]''.\n\nOn the December 7, 2013, episode of ''[[Saturday Night Live]]'', as part of the opening monologue, comedian and host [[Paul Rudd]] performed a portion of the song a cappella with boy band musical guest [[One Direction]], [[Will Ferrell]], [[David Koechner]], and [[Steve Carell]]---in a fashion similar to the song in ''Anchorman''---to promote ''[[Anchorman 2: The Legend Continues]]''.\n\nIt appeared in a [[2014 in television|2014]] [[TV commercial]] for [[Taco Bell]].\n\nOn July 4, 1976 it was featured as the theme song for CBS's all day Bicentennial coverage hosted by [[Dan Rather]].\n\n==See also==\n*[[List_of_one-hit_wonders_in_the_United_States#1970s|List of 1970s one-hit wonders in the United States]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{MetroLyrics song|starland-vocal-band|afternoon-delight}}<!-- Licensed lyrics provider -->\n* {{cite news|last=du Lac|first=J. Freedom|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/arts-and-entertainment/wp/2018/07/10/skyrockets-in-flight-afternoon-delight-the-story-behind-starland-vocal-bands-one-big-hit/|title=Starland Vocal Band\u2019s \u2018Afternoon Delight\u2019 still being served after 35 years|work=The Washington Post|date=July 8, 2011|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160609232810/http://www.washingtonpost.com/local/starland-vocal-bands-afternoon-delight-still-being-served-after-35-years/2011/06/28/gIQA5VCl3H_story.html|archivedate=June 9, 2016}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Afternoon Delight (Song)}}\n[[Category:1976 debut singles]]\n[[Category:Billboard Hot 100 number-one singles]]\n[[Category:Johnny Carver songs]]\n[[Category:Songs about sexuality]]\n[[Category:Starland Vocal Band songs]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Bill Danoff]]\n[[Category:Grammy Award for Best Vocal Arrangement for Two or More Voices]]\n[[Category:1976 songs]]\n[[Category:RCA Records singles]]\n[[Category:Song recordings produced by Milt Okun]]\n[[Category:Country pop songs]]\n", "text_old": "{{other uses}}\n{{Infobox song\n| name       = Afternoon Delight\n| cover      = Afternoon Delight by The Starland Vocal Band.jpg\n| alt        =\n| type       = single\n| artist     = [[Starland Vocal Band]]\n| album      = Starland Vocal Band\n| B-side     = Starland\n| released   = April 1976\n| format     = [[7-inch single]]\n| recorded   = November 1975\n| studio     =\n| venue      =\n| genre      = [[Country pop]], [[soft rock]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.stereogum.com/5507/40_most_softsational_softrock_songs/franchises/list/|title=VH1\u2019s 40 Most Softsational Soft-Rock Songs|date=May 31, 2007|website=[[Stereogum]]|publisher=[[SpinMedia]]|access-date=July 31, 2016}}</ref>\n| length     = 3:16\n| label      =\n*[[Windstar Records|Windsong]] (US)\n*[[Leon Schlesinger|Windlands International]] (UK & Canada)\n| writer     = [[Bill Danoff]]\n| producer   = [[Milt Okun]]\n| prev_title =\n| prev_year  =\n| next_title = California Day\n| next_year  = 1976\n| misc       = {{external music video|header=Audio|{{youtube|XHMi_5a9Omg|\"Afternoon Delight\"}}}}\n}}\n\n\"'''Afternoon Delight'''\" is a hit song recorded by [[Starland Vocal Band]], known for its [[close harmony]] and sexually suggestive wordplay. It was written by [[Bill Danoff]], one of the members of the band.\n\n\"Afternoon Delight\" charted well in New Zealand, peaking at number five. In Australia it was a number-six hit ([[Adelaide]] radio station [[5MMM|5KA]] was first to pick up the single, making it number one in [[South Australia]]). In the UK, it reached number 18 and was used as theme to a weekly show of the same title on London's [[Capital London|Capital Radio]], hosted by [[Duncan Johnson]], and from 1980 on an afternoon show using the same title, broadcast every weekday at [[Mercia Sound]] in [[Coventry]], presented by [[Stuart Linnell]]. It became a US number-one single on July 10, 1976<ref name=\"Bronson\">{{cite book  | last = Bronson  | first = Fred  | authorlink = Fred Bronson  | title = The Billboard Book of Number 1 Hits  | edition = 5th  | year = 2003  | publisher = Billboard Books  | isbn = 0-8230-7677-6  | page = 438  | url = https://books.google.com/books?id=PgGqNrqfrsoC&pg=PT447&dq=%22Afternoon+Delight%22+0823076776&ei=BvTuS865DaHCzQT74t3GCg&cd=1#v=onepage&q&f=false  | chapter = Afternoon Delight}}</ref> and earned a [[Music recording sales certification|gold record]]. \"Afternoon Delight\" also reached number one in Canada.\n\n==Background and writing==\nThe title came from the [[happy hour]] menu at [[Clyde's Restaurant Group|Clyde's]] [[restaurant]] in [[Georgetown (Washington, D.C.)|Georgetown]], [[Washington, D.C.]]<ref name=\"Bronson\"/> where Bill Danoff was eating with fellow bandmember Margot Chapman while his then-wife [[Taffy Danoff]] was undergoing surgery for [[cervical cancer]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://patch.com/florida/safetyharbor/grammy-winner-taffy-nivert-settles-in-safety-harbor |title=Grammy Winner Taffy Nivert Settles In Safety Harbor - Safety Harbor, FL Patch |website=Patch.com |date=2013-02-08 |accessdate=2016-10-11}}</ref> Danoff enjoyed writing the song and downplayed the somewhat controversial lyrics, saying, \"I didn't want to write an all-out [[sexual intercourse|sex]] song ... I just wanted to write something that was fun and hinted at sex.\"<ref name=\"Bronson\"/>\n\n==Cover versions==\nConcurrent with the Starland Vocal Band version, country singer [[Johnny Carver (musician)|Johnny Carver]]'s cover went Top 10 on ''Billboard'' [[Hot Country Songs|Hot Country Singles]]. In 1983, the [[Circle Jerks]] also covered it as one of the six covers on \"Golden Shower of Hits (Jerks on 45)\", which appears on their album ''[[Golden Shower of Hits]]''. British experimental folk music band [[Current 93]] used an industrial-style cover as an introduction to performances of their 2009 album. [[Claude Fran\u00e7ois]] sang it in French as \"Dimanche apr\u00e8s-midi\". The popular TV show ''[[Glee (TV series)|Glee]]'' also covered it in their episode \"[[Sexy (Glee)|Sexy]]\", with [[Dianna Agron]], [[Jayma Mays]], [[Mark Salling]], [[Lea Michele]], and [[John Stamos]] singing.\n\n==Critical reaction==\nAt the [[19th Grammy Awards]] ceremony in 1977, \"Afternoon Delight\" received three nominations for recordings from 1976. It won the [[Grammy Award for Best Vocal Arrangement for Two or More Voices|Grammy Award for Best Arrangement for Voices]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.grammy.com/nominees/search?artist=starland+vocal+band&title=&year=All&genre=All |title=The Grammys : Starland Vocal Band : Search |website=Grammy.com |accessdate=2016-10-11}}</ref> and was also nominated for Best Pop Performance by a Duo or Group with Vocals and [[Grammy Award for Song of the Year|Song of the Year]].\n\nIn 2010 ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' named \"Afternoon Delight\" the 20th sexiest song of all time.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/959429/the-50-sexiest-songs-of-all-time-page-4 |title=The 50 Sexiest Songs Of All Time Page 4 |publisher=Billboard |date= |accessdate=2016-10-11}}</ref>\n\n==Chart performance==\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-2}}\n\n===Weekly charts===\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n!Chart (1976)\n!Peak<br />position\n|-\n| Australian Singles Chart\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|6\n|-\n|Canada ''[[RPM (magazine)|RPM]]'' Top Singles<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bac-lac.gc.ca/eng/discover/films-videos-sound-recordings/rpm/Pages/image.aspx?Image=nlc008388.4299a&URLjpg=http%3a%2f%2fwww.collectionscanada.gc.ca%2fobj%2f028020%2ff4%2fnlc008388.4299a.gif&Ecopy=nlc008388.4299a|title=Item Display - RPM - Library and Archives Canada |website=Collectionscanada.gc.ca |date=1976-08-07 |accessdate=2018-06-10}}</ref>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|1\n|-\n|Canada ''RPM'' Adult Contemporary<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bac-lac.gc.ca/eng/discover/films-videos-sound-recordings/rpm/Pages/image.aspx?Image=nlc008388.4151&URLjpg=http%3a%2f%2fwww.collectionscanada.gc.ca%2fobj%2f028020%2ff4%2fnlc008388.4151.gif&Ecopy=nlc008388.4151|title=Item Display - RPM - Library and Archives Canada |website=Collectionscanada.gc.ca |date=1976-07-10 |accessdate=2018-06-11}}</ref>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|6\n|-\n{{single chart|Dutch100|22|artist=Starland Vocal Band |song=Afternoon Delight}}\n|-\n{{single chart|New Zealand|5|artist=Starland Vocal Band |song=Afternoon Delight}}\n|-\n{{single chart|UKsinglesbyname|18|artist=Starland Vocal Band}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Billboardhot100|1|artist=Starland Vocal Band}}\n|-\n| US [[Adult Contemporary (chart)|Easy Listening]] (''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'')<ref>[https://www.billboard.com/music/Starland-Vocal-Band/chart-history/adult-contemporary \"Starland Vocal Band Chart History (Easy Listening)\"]. ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]''.</ref>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|5\n|-\n{{single chart|Billboardcountrysongs|94|artist=Starland Vocal Band}}\n|}\n{{col-2}}\n\n===Year-end charts===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Chart (1976)\n! Rank\n|-\n|Australia<ref name=\"australian-charts.com\">[http://australian-charts.com/forum.asp?todo=viewthread&id=40275 Australian-charts.com] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141006134948/http://australian-charts.com/forum.asp?todo=viewthread&id=40275 |date=2014-10-06 }}</ref>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|56\n|-\n|Canada ''RPM'' Top Singles<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.collectionscanada.gc.ca/rpm/028020-119.01-e.php?&file_num=nlc008388.5173a&type=1&interval=20&PHPSESSID=u9874ano8k0c5b6bkp4r8qrbp3 |title= Top Singles \u2013 Volume 26, No. 14 & 15, January 08 1977 |work= [[RPM (magazine)|RPM]] |publisher= [[Library and Archives Canada]] |accessdate= December 6, 2017 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20160319222559/http://www.collectionscanada.gc.ca/rpm/028020-119.01-e.php?&file_num=nlc008388.5173a&type=1&interval=20&PHPSESSID=u9874ano8k0c5b6bkp4r8qrbp3 |archive-date= 2016-03-19 |url-status= dead }}</ref>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|11\n|-\n|New Zealand <ref>http://nztop40.co.nz/chart/?chart=3865</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|28\n|-\n|UK <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.old-charts.com/charts70/yearend70/1976yearend_uk.htm |title=Old-Charts |publisher=Old-Charts |date= |accessdate=2015-11-12}}</ref>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|120\n|-\n|US ''Billboard'' Hot 100<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.musicoutfitters.com/topsongs/1976.htm |title=Top 100 Hits of 1976/Top 100 Songs of 1976 |website=Musicoutfitters.com |date= |accessdate=2016-10-11}}</ref>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|12\n|-\n|US ''Billboard'' Easy Listening<ref>[http://www.45cat.com/45_list_view_record.php?li=2171 Top 50 Adult Contemporary Hits of 1976]</ref>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|31\n|-\n|US ''Cash Box'' Top 100<ref>{{cite web|url=http://50.6.195.142/archives/70s_files/1976YESP.html |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2016-06-05 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141021102718/http://50.6.195.142/archives/70s_files/1976YESP.html |archivedate=2014-10-21 }}</ref>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|7\n|}\n\n===All-time charts===\n{|class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\"\n|-\n! Chart (1958-2018)\n! Position\n|-\n|US ''Billboard'' Hot 100<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/charts/hot-100-60th-anniversary|title=Billboard Hot 100 60th Anniversary Interactive Chart|work=Billboard|accessdate=10 December 2018}}</ref>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|419\n|}\n{{col-end}}\n\n=== Johnny Carver version ===\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Chart (1976)\n! Peak<br />position\n|-\n| US ''Billboard'' Hot Country Singles & Tracks\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|9\n|-\n| Canadian ''RPM'' Country Tracks\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|16\n|}\n\n==In popular culture==\n{{unreferenced section|date=September 2017}}\n{{reduce trivia|section|date=September 2017}}\nSince the original song's release, many works have alluded to or even featured \"Afternoon Delight\" or its suggestive lyrics. Among them have been ''[[Cocktail (1988 film)|Cocktail]]'' (\"[[Kokomo (song)|Kokomo]]\", sung by [[The Beach Boys]]), ''[[Glee (TV series)|Glee]]'' (where it was mistaken as a song celebrating America's 1976 Bicentennial), ''[[Get a Life (TV series)|Get a Life]]'' (\"Chris Wins a Celebrity\"), ''[[Good Will Hunting]]'', ''[[PCU (film)|PCU]]'' (forced listening as a form of torture), ''[[Boogie Nights]]'', ''[[Lost (TV series)|Lost]]'', ''[[The Rules of Attraction]]'', ''[[The Spirit of '76 (1990 film)|The Spirit of '76]]'', ''[[Starsky & Hutch (film)|Starsky & Hutch]]'', ''[[ER (season 9)|ER]]'' (\"No Strings Attached\", sung by [[Abby Lockhart|Abby]]), ''[[Arrested Development (TV series)|Arrested Development]]'' (as part of a plot point in the episode \"[[Afternoon Delight (Arrested Development episode)|Afternoon Delight]]\"), ''[[The Simpsons]]'' (\"[[The Fat and the Furriest]]\"), ''[[Rules of Engagement (TV series)|Rules of Engagement]]'', ''[[Sports Night]]'', ''[[Complete Savages]]'' (\"Teen Things I Hate About You\"), ''[[Ugly Betty]]'', ''[[Family Guy]]'', ''[[Malcolm in the Middle]]'', ''[[South Park]]'' (\"[[Miss Teacher Bangs a Boy]]\"), ''[[Murphy Brown]]'', ''[[Entourage (U.S. TV series)|Entourage]]'', ''[[Warehouse 13]]'' (Season 2 Episode 8), ''[[Teenage Caveman (2002 film)|Teenage Caveman]]'' and ''[[Anchorman: The Legend of Ron Burgundy]]''.\n\nOn the December 7, 2013, episode of ''[[Saturday Night Live]]'', as part of the opening monologue, comedian and host [[Paul Rudd]] performed a portion of the song a cappella with boy band musical guest [[One Direction]], [[Will Ferrell]], [[David Koechner]], and [[Steve Carell]]---in a fashion similar to the song in ''Anchorman''---to promote ''[[Anchorman 2: The Legend Continues]]''.\n\nIt appeared in a [[2014 in television|2014]] [[TV commercial]] for [[Taco Bell]].\n\nOn July 4, 1976 it was featured as the theme song for CBS's all day Bicentennial coverage hosted by [[Dan Rather]].\n\n==See also==\n*[[List_of_one-hit_wonders_in_the_United_States#1970s|List of 1970s one-hit wonders in the United States]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{MetroLyrics song|starland-vocal-band|afternoon-delight}}<!-- Licensed lyrics provider -->\n* {{cite news|last=du Lac|first=J. Freedom|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/arts-and-entertainment/wp/2018/07/10/skyrockets-in-flight-afternoon-delight-the-story-behind-starland-vocal-bands-one-big-hit/|title=Starland Vocal Band\u2019s \u2018Afternoon Delight\u2019 still being served after 35 years|work=The Washington Post|date=July 8, 2011|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160609232810/http://www.washingtonpost.com/local/starland-vocal-bands-afternoon-delight-still-being-served-after-35-years/2011/06/28/gIQA5VCl3H_story.html|archivedate=June 9, 2016}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Afternoon Delight (Song)}}\n[[Category:1976 debut singles]]\n[[Category:Billboard Hot 100 number-one singles]]\n[[Category:Johnny Carver songs]]\n[[Category:Songs about sexuality]]\n[[Category:Starland Vocal Band songs]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Bill Danoff]]\n[[Category:Grammy Award for Best Vocal Arrangement for Two or More Voices]]\n[[Category:1976 songs]]\n[[Category:RCA Records singles]]\n[[Category:Song recordings produced by Milt Okun]]\n[[Category:Country pop songs]]\n", "name_user": "JGabbard", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eJohnny Carver version:-w", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Afternoon_Delight"}
